Ing '''Tiruchirappalli''' ({{lang-ta|தி௫ச்சிராப்பள்ளி}}) {{audio|Tiruchirapalli.ogg|pronunciation}} a misusulat muring '''Tiruchirapalli''', at karaniwan dang ausang '''Tiruchi''' o '''Trichy''' ({{lang-ta|தி௫ச்சி}}), a agkas dang '''Trichinopoly''' aniang [[:en:British Empire|panaun ning pamaniakup ing Britania]]., ing kapat a pekamaragul <ref>[http://www.trichy.com/] </ref> a lakanbalen o ciudad ning [[Tamil Nadu]] kaibat ning [[Chennai]], [[Madurai]] ampong [[Coimbatore]]. Atiu king libutad ning estadu, kareng pampang ning [[Ilug Cauvery]]. Metung yang [[:en:municipal corporation]], at pun tanggapan neng pangkapanibalan (''administrative headquarters'') ne ning [[Distritu ning Tiruchirapalli]].

Ing pikabaluan nang diling tanda ning Trichy ya pin ing templuing kutang batu (''rock fort temple'') a makalual o makabural. Deng Pallavas ing minunang dinukit kaniti, dapot deng [[Nayaks ning Madurai]] deng ginawa ketang templung kutang batu. Makatagulaling ya kang Ginung [[Shiva]] ampong Ginung [[Ganesha]] ing templu.<ref name="India">India By Sarina Singh, Joe Bindloss, Paul Clammer, Janine Eberle</ref>.

Atiu king lakanbalen ning Trichy ing [[Srirangam]], metung a templung [[Vaishnavite]] a pekamaragul a templung [[Hindu]]ng magagamit pa king mabilug a yatu. Atiu murin king Trichy ing "ThiruAnaikka" ([[ThiruvAnaikkaval]]), metung kareng limang tuknanan ("Panchaboodha Sthalam") nang Ginung [[Shiva]]. Mibait ya king Thiruvanaikaval i [[Chandrasekhara Venkata Raman]], at atiu pa murin ing kayang bale, a metung nang museu ngeni.

